BuildPro - Construction Company Website
A modern, responsive construction company website built with React, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS.

Features
ğŸ  Home Page: Showcasing company services, stats, and featured projects
ğŸ—ï¸ Projects Gallery: Browse all construction projects with filtering
ğŸ˜ï¸ Property Listings: Explore available properties with search and filters
ğŸ“± Responsive Design: Works seamlessly on desktop, tablet, and mobile
ğŸ¨ Modern UI: Built with shadcn/ui components and Tailwind CSS
âš¡ Fast Performance: Optimized build with Vite
Tech Stack
Frontend: React 18 + TypeScript
Styling: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
Build Tool: Vite
Routing: React Router v6
Icons: Lucide React
Installation
Extract the archive:
tar -xzf buildpro-website.tar.gz
cd buildpro-website
Install dependencies:
pnpm install
# or
npm install
# or
yarn install
Start development server:
pnpm run dev
# or
npm run dev
# or
yarn dev
The website will be available at http://localhost:5173

Build for Production
pnpm run build
# or
npm run build
# or
yarn build
The production-ready files will be in the dist/ directory.

Deployment
Deploy to Your Own Server
Build the project:
pnpm run build
Upload the dist/ folder to your web server

Configure your web server to serve the index.html file for all routes (for React Router to work)

Deploy to Vercel
# Install Vercel CLI
npm i -g vercel

# Deploy
vercel
Deploy to Netlify
# Install Netlify CLI
npm i -g netlify-cli

# Deploy
netlify deploy --prod --dir=dist
